Gas leak at Norzink plant but zinc output normal . A leak of sulphurous gas on Wednesday at Norzink ' s zinc plant at Odda in southwest Norway did not affect production , a company spokesman said . The gas leak at a sulphuric acid unit was detected early on Wednesday , said Knut Terje Solstad . " We have stopped operations at that part of the plant to investigate the leak and repair the damage to a ventilation system . But it will only be for a few hours . Production of zinc is normal , " Solstad said . Norzink expects to produce 140 , 000 tonnes at Odda in 1996 . The company is jointly owned by RTZ Corp Plc and Trelleborg AB . - - Oslo newsroom , + 47 22 42 50 41 
